<HEADLINE> Iran Impounds Iraqi Oil Tankers  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CAIRO, Egypt (AP) -- Iranian authorities have impounded two Iraqi
tankers suspected of smuggling Iraqi oil, according to Iranian
state radio.
</P>
<P>
   The tankers had anchored off the Iranian island of Kish in the
southern Gulf several days ago, the Voice of the Islamic Republic
of Iran said Tuesday night in a bulletin monitored by the British
Broadcasting Corp.
</P>
<P>
   The report said the tankers lacked proper documentation and
entered Iran's waters without permission carrying ''smuggled Iraqi
oil.'' It added that a previously impounded tanker was still
anchored off Kish.
</P>
<P>
   It was not possible to obtain an immediate response from the
Iraqi authorities.
</P>
<P>
   The United Nations imposed sanctions after Iraq invaded Kuwait
in 1990. Officials of the U.S. 5th Fleet, which enforces U.N.
sanctions against Iraq in the Persian Gulf, have said that Iraqi
ships evade the embargo by sailing down the Persian Gulf in Iranian
waters.
</P>
