<HEADLINE> NATO Names Atlantic Commander  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) -- NATO said Wednesday it has appointed
Lt. Gen. William F. Kernan of the U.S. Army to be the new supreme
allied commander, Atlantic, one of two strategic command posts in
the 19-nation defense alliance.
</P>
<P>
   Kernan, who has been nominated by President Clinton for his
fourth star, will replace Adm. Harold W. Gehman, Jr. in September
at Atlantic command headquarters in Norfolk, Va.
</P>
<P>
   The other strategic command post -- supreme allied commander,
Europe, based in southern Belgium -- currently is held by U.S. Air
Force Gen. Joseph W. Ralston. He replaced Gen. Wesley K. Clark in
May.
</P>
