<HEADLINE> Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   In the birthday spotlight:
</P>
<P>
   Director John Woo had a mission: to comfort Tom Cruise's mother
when he sent his leading man up a cliff for a dizzying climbing
scene. They watched the ''Mission: Impossible 2'' star climb an
overhanging cliff some 2,000 feet above ground without a safety
net. Cruise did that stunt seven times, and his mother and Woo
''worried 70 times,'' the director said. ''I kept sweating. I
closed my eyes and prayed to God.'' Cruise, who was born on July 3,
1962, said he would like to work with Woo again because ''he takes
action and elevates it beyond the way that we knew before.''
</P>
<P>
   TV talk-show host Montel Williams skipped the platitudes and
challenged graduates to turn around ''a nation that doesn't really
care'' in a recent commencement address at Lehigh University in
Bethlehem, Pa. Citing adversity in his own life as a tough lesson
in compassion, Williams urged the grads to define success by
helping others as they had been helped in their own lives.
Williams, host of the nationally syndicated ''Montel Williams
Show,'' placed little hope in politicians to help close what he
called a growing gap between rich and poor. He was born on July 3,
1956.
</P>
<P>
   Celebrity birthdays for July 2-8:
</P>
<P>
   July 2: Actor Ron Silver is 54. Musician Roy Bittan of Bruce
Springsteen and the E Street Band is 51. Musician Dave Parsons of
Bush is 35.
</P>
