<HEADLINE> Reactions to Court's Abortion Vote  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Reactions to Wednesday's 5-4 Supreme Court ruling
striking down
Nebraska's law banning so-called ''partial-birth'' abortions:
<TEXT>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   ''There has never been a greater need to speak out against the
barbaric procedure of 'partial-birth' abortion.'' -- American Center
for Law and Justice.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   ''While it looks like a victory, this is a beginning -- not the
end. Anti-choice state legislatures and governors across the
country will use this ruling as a blueprint for drafting new bans
on abortion procedures -- laws which will soon be tested by the
Supreme Court once again.'' -- Planned Parenthood.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   ''Ten, 15 or 20 years from now, today's Supreme Court decision
will be cited to justify the selective termination of infants,
toddlers, grandparents and the disabled.'' -- American Life League.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   ''This so-called 'partial-birth' abortion ban was a direct
assault on Roe v. Wade and the Supreme Court was right to reject
it. Americans support Roe because they don't want the government or
politicians interfering in this most private and personal
decision.'' -- National Women's Law Center.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   ''I look forward to the day when a Republican president will
replace retiring liberals with justices who will truthfully
interpret the Constitution rather than impose their activist views
against states and the people.'' Rep. J.C. Watts of Oklahoma,
chairman of the House Republican Conference.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   ''Today, women's health prevailed over extremism. By reaffirming
Roe v. Wade, the court has upheld a woman's basic constitutional
right to make private, personal decisions.'' Sen. Barbara Boxer,
D-Calif.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   ''A procedure in which a child is intentionally killed in the
birth canal can only be described as infanticide. It is astounding
that the court would allow a doctor to pull a defenseless child
from its mother's womb, pierce its skull and suck out its brain.''
-- Council on American-Islamic Relations.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   ''This is a great day for American women. 'Partial-birth'
abortion laws do not primarily involve late-term abortions, and the
U.S. Supreme Court has unmasked the false propaganda effort of the
anti-choice movement as being unconstitutional and inconsistent
with the fundamental liberty interests of women.'' -- Former New
York State Attorney General Bob Abrams, one of a group of attorneys
who filed a friend-of-the-court brief.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   ''The Supreme Court's decision today, in Stenberg v. Carhart, to
strike down the state of Nebraska's ban on 'partial-birth'
abortions represents a stunning rejection of the role of medicine
and science in helping to decide our nation's abortion policies.''
-- Physicians Ad Hoc Coalition for Truth.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   ''The court's decision in Stenberg v. Carhart exposed these bans
for what they are: extreme and deceptive attempts to outlaw
abortion, even early in pregnancy, that jeopardize women's health.
The court's decision will have the domino effect of rendering
similar bans passed in over 30 states and Congress unconstitutional
or unenforceable.''-- Center for Reproductive Law and Policy.
</P>
</TEXT>
