<HEADLINE> RETRANSMITTING  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   PINE PLAINS, N.Y. (AP) - A Connecticut man was killed when the
frame of a Ferris wheel collapsed while he was assembling it for a
carnival.
</P>
<P>
   A second man sustained minor injuries in the Monday incident.
</P>
<P>
   Samuel Rosado Morales, 23, of Danbury, was crushed by the frame
of a section of the ride, acording to state police at Millbrook. He
was pronounced dead at Sharon Hospital in Connecticut.
</P>
<P>
   The two men were assembling the Ferris wheel on the grounds of
St. Anthonys Church in preparation for a carnival being held as a
fund-raiser for the Pine Plains Fire Department.
</P>
<P>
   There was no sign of foul play and the incident may have been
the result of human error, said state Police Senior Investigator
Thomas Maher. An investigation was continuing.
</P>
<P>
   The rides are operated by Country Amusements Inc. of Newtown,
Conn.
</P>
</TEXT>
