and a bit of publicity -- for $7.5 million.
</P>
<P>
   The five-member Burgundians are backed by an unnamed investor
whose identity will be revealed on closing day, July 12, said group
publicist Dindy Yokel. A $750,000 cash deposit is being held in
escrow.
</P>
