<HEADLINE> Three U.S. Crews Win at Henley  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HENLEY ON THAMES, England (AP) -- Three U.S. crews -- from
Washingston state, Virginia and Massachusetts -- were among the
winners Wednesday on the opening day of racing at Henley Royal
Regatta on the Thames.
</P>
<P>
   In the Thames Cup for club eights, the Cascade club from Seattle
broke to a strong start and downed Nottingham of England by 2&AMP;frac14;
lengths. They next face the English club Molesey, with the field
down to 16.
</P>
<P>
   The Temple Cup for student eights produced an all-U.S. opening
heat, with the Virginia Rowing Association from Charlottesville
defeating Colby College in Maine by five lengths.
</P>
<P>
   Virginia faces the seeded English crew from Nottingham
University in the second round.
</P>
<P>
   In the Princess Elizabeth Cup for schoolboy eights, the Groton
School from Massachusetts was too strong for the King's School
Canterbury, England, winning by 4&AMP;frac12; lengths in the opening heat.
</P>
<P>
   They face stiffer opposition from England in the last 16 in the
shape of Canford School.
</P>
<P>
   The Britannia Cup is for coxed fours. In the opening round,
Rutgers was beaten by 2&AMP;frac34; lengths by Lea from London. Bowdoin of
Maine lost by three-quarters of a length to London Rowing Club.
</P>
<P>
   Canadian club Brock also lost its opening race in the Britannia
Cup, beaten by 1&AMP;frac34; lengths by Imperial College from London.
</P>
</TEXT>
