<HEADLINE> State Fair will be part of first lady's summer  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   SYRACUSE, N.Y. (AP) - Senate candidate Hillary Rodham Clinton
promised Wednesday to make a return visit to the State Fair held
annually here.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'll be back at the state fair, absolutely,'' the first lady
told an enthusiastic crowd of more than 300 at a union hall in
Syracuse.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier in the day, she told supporters during a stop at a
bakery she also planned to spend at least a few days this summer in
Skaneateles, near Syracuse.
</P>
<P>
   The first lady, President Clinton and daughter Chelsea,
vacationed last year in Skaneateles, a resort community 16 miles
southwest of Syracuse.
</P>
<P>
   This year's fair runs Aug. 24-Sept. 4.
</P>
</TEXT>
