<HEADLINE> Orioles Acquire Cardinals Reliever  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BALTIMORE (AP) -- The Baltimore Orioles acquired right-handed
reliever Darren Holmes from the St. Louis Cardinals on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   An Orioles spokesman said Holmes was signed to a minor-league
contract and will report to Triple-A Rochester. The teams have not
yet agreed what St. Louis will receive in the deal.
</P>
<P>
   Holmes (0-1) has struggled in the majors this season, pitching
in five games for the Cardinals and four games for the Arizona
Diamondbacks.
</P>
<P>
   He was sent from St. Louis to Triple-A Memphis on June 1.
</P>
</TEXT>
