<HEADLINE> Chargers Sign Deon Humphrey  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Linebacker Deon Humphrey, who played this year
in NFL Europe for the Amsterdam Admirals, agreed Wednesday to a
one-year contract with the San Diego Chargers.
</P>
<P>
   Humphrey had 26 tackles, one-half sack, broke up four passes,
forced a fumble and had eight tackles on special teams during the
2000 NFL Europe season.
</P>
<P>
   He spent the 1999 season on the Green Bay Packers practice squad
after originally joining the team as a rookie free agent. Humphrey
was a four-year letterman (1995-98) at Florida State, recording 80
tackles and one sack.
