<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-28 18:32 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France 2, Portugal 1, OT  </HEADLINE>
By ANDREAS EVAGORA
<TEXT>
<P>
   BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) -- Zinedine Zidane made a penalty kick
with three minutes left in overtime as World Cup champion France
beat Portugal 2-1 Wednesday to reach the final at the European
Soccer Championship.
</P>
<P>
   After Portugal's Abel Xavier used his left hand to block Sylvain
Wiltord's angled shot, Zidane stepped up to shoot the ball into the
top corner and out of goalkeeper Vitor Baia's reach.
</P>
<P>
   ''In the last minute, it was tough to concentrate,'' said
Zidane, who scored twice in the 1998 World Cup final.
</P>
<P>
   ''It was the knockout punch.''
</P>
<P>
   In chaotic scenes afterward, with Portuguese players protesting,
referee Guenther Benko ejected Nuno Gomes, whose fourth goal of the
tournament gave Portugal a 1-0 lead in the first half.
</P>
<P>
   Portuguese coach Humberto Coelho announced his resignation after
the game. ''It was an unfortunate decision,'' Coelho said of the
referee's awarding of the penalty kick.
</P>
<P>
   In the 19th minute, Sergio Conceicao stole the ball from Didier
Deschamps and passed it to Nuno Gomes, who quickly turned and fired
in a 16-yard shot.
</P>
<P>
   France made it 1-1 six minutes into the second half. Nicolas
Anelka, seemingly offside, was allowed to turn around and pass back
to Thierry Henry, who shot the ball in from 10 yards out.
</P>
<P>
   The French were saved by goalkeeper Fabien Barthez with a minute
left in regulation, when he palmed Abel Xavier's header over the
crossbar.
</P>
<P>
   ''It was really tough for us,'' 1998 FIFA world player of the
year Zidane said. ''The Portuguese were great.''
</P>
<P>
   The action was frenetic in overtime.
</P>
<P>
   Zidane almost gave France the victory one minute in, but his
header sailed high. French defender Laurent Blanc had the same
thing happen six minutes later. Sa Pinto's long shot flew just wide
for Portugal in the 20th minute of overtime.
</P>
<P>
   The Netherlands plays Italy in the other semifinal Thursday in
Amsterdam. The final is Sunday at Rotterdam, Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
   ''Our objective was not to be in the final. It is to win the
final,'' Zidane said.
</P>
<P>
   France came into Euro 2000 trying to become the first world
champion to also hold the European title. And the team's tough
defense eventually wore down the Portuguese.
</P>
<P>
   Gomes' score was Portugal's lone shot on goal in the first hour.
</P>
<P>
   French president Jacques Chirac was among the 50,000 fans at the
King Baudouin Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   Italy takes a 6-2-5 record against the Dutch into the other
semifinal. Both countries have won the European Championship once.
</P>
<P>
   ''Our strength is our patience,'' Italian defender Alessandro
Nesta said. ''We have a great history behind us and all the teams
hope they won't come up against Italy.''
</P>
<P>
   Italy will be able to field captain Paolo Maldini, who has
recovered after straining his thigh in a 2-0 quarterfinal victory
over Romania.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-28-00 1832 </TRAILER>
