<BODY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Storms speckled the Southeast and Plains and the West
stayed
fair and dry Wednesday, while partly to mostly cloudy skies covered
the Northeast.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Scattered showers and thunderstorms stretched from Maryland and
Delaware, through Virginia, Kentucky and Tennessee, with the
strongest storms packing locally heavy downpours across easterain
Tennessee and westerain Virginia.
</P>
<P>
   A warm, moist and unstable air mass covered most of the
Southeast and along the Gulf Coast, and showers and thunderstorms
started forming over southerain Louisiana, Mississippi, Alabama and
Florida.
</P>
<P>
   Most of the remainder of the Southeast saw a mix of sun and
clouds.
</P>
<P>
   A large area of rain and thunderstorms lingered in southerain
Missouri, westerain Arkansas, Oklahoma and the Texas Panhandle, with
the heaviest rainfall falling occurring in easterain Oklahoma and
northwesterain Arkansas.
</P>
<P>
   Two to four inches of rain pelted those areas, and flash flood
warainings were in effect for Oklahoma's Adair, Cherokee and Delaware
counties and Benton and Washington counties in Arkansas.
</P>
<P>
   ''I was looking for fish to be going across the highway,'' said
Sandy Stafford, a clerk at the Seminole County Sheriff's Department
in Wewoka in central Oklahoma.
</P>
<P>
   Less intense showers and thunderstorms remained in the southerain
Plains, and a few light showers moved across parts of Iowa,
southerain Wisconsin and northerain Illinois. Rainfall amounts totaled
less than a tenth of an inch.
</P>
<P>
   The rest of the northerain and central Plains, as well as the
Great Lakes and Ohio Valley were under partly cloudy skies.
</P>
<P>
   Most of the westerain United States had fair, dry weather. The
exception: some of the Southwest and southerain Rockies, where there
were clouds and scattered showers.
</P>
<P>
   Temperatures around the Lower 48 on Wednesday ranged from 99
degrees in Las Vegas to 34 in Leadville, Colo.
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   National Weather Service:
http://iwin.nws.noaa.gov/iwin/graphicsversion/bigmain.html
</P>
<P>
   Intellicast: http://www.intellicast.com/LocalWeather
</P>
<P>
   Weather Channel: http://www.weather.com
</P>
<P>
   UM Weather (University of Michigan):
http://cirrus.sprl.umich.edu/wxnet
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
