<HEADLINE> Gonzalez Scratched Over Sore Foot  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DETROIT (AP) -- Juan Gonzalez was a late scratch from the Detroit
Tigers' lineup against the New York Yankees on Wednesday night with
a recurrence of soreness in his left foot.
</P>
<P>
   Gonzalez was injured Saturday night in Cleveland when he fouled
a pitch off his foot. He didn't play Sunday at Cleveland but was
back in the lineup Tuesday, going 0-for-6 against the Yankees in
the Tigers' 7-6, 11-inning win.
</P>
<P>
   Tuesday's game was the Tigers' first after a proposed trade that
would have sent Gonzalez to the Yankees fell through. He was
supposed to be Detroit's designated hitter Wednesday but was
scratched shortly before game time.
</P>
<P>
   Gonzalez is batting .264 with 13 home runs and 31 RBIs.
</P>
</TEXT>
