<HEADLINE> Mendoza Goes on DL  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DETROIT (AP) -- Right-hander Ramiro Mendoza, scheduled to start
for the New York Yankees on Thursday night at Detroit, was placed
on the 15-day disabled list Wednesday with weakness in the back of
his right shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Yankees manager Joe Torre said left-hander Andy Pettitte, who
pitched Sunday at Chicago, will start Thursday on three days' rest.
No other roster move was announced.
</P>
<P>
   Mendoza (7-3, 3.72 ERA) joins right-handers Roger Clemens and
Orlando Hernandez on the Yankees' injury list. But Torre said
there's some hope that either Clemens or Hernandez or both could
return by this weekend's series at Tampa Bay.
</P>
<P>
   Clemens, on the disabled list since June 15 with a strained
right groin, was scheduled to throw batting practice Thursday at
Tampa, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Hernandez hasn't pitched since he sprained his right elbow June
18 against Chicago. He'll work out Thursday in Detroit, and Torre
said he'll go on the disabled list if he's not ready to pitch by
the weekend.
</P>
