</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000628.0240 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-28 19:53 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dodgers' Shaw Put on DL  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Los Angeles Dodgers closer Jeff Shaw was
placed on the disabled list Wednesday for the first time in his
career because of tendinitis in his right elbow.
</P>
<P>
   The move is retroactive to June 27. Replacing Shaw on the roster
is right-hander Jamie Arnold, who was recalled from Triple-A
Albuquerque.
</P>
<P>
   ''Fourteen years I've been playing this game and I've never been
on the DL. Never. Not even close,'' Shaw said. ''I wrestled with
this for three or four days. When I came here yesterday, it was
like, 'All right, let's just get it done, do it, get it over
with.'''
</P>
<P>
   Shaw felt tightness in his elbow on Saturday morning, after
allowing four hits in 1 1-3 innings at St. Louis the night before.
He pitched once after that, allowing a run in the ninth inning
Monday night against San Diego.
</P>
<P>
   Shaw, who had 124 saves over the previous four seasons, has 12
in 19 opportunities and an 8.00 ERA in 29 outings overall this
year.
</P>
<P>
   He was given 1&AMP;frac12; weeks of rest earlier this season by manager
Davey Johnson because of what Shaw described as a knot behind his
shoulder. He was eased back into the closer role after that
episode, and anticipates the same thing will happen when he is
eligible to come off the DL after the All-Star break.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'd say it would depend on the situation,'' Shaw said.
''Davey's been talking about matchups, so it's going to be a thing
where if I go out and convert a couple, it's going to be right back
to where we were before.''
</P>
<P>
   Arnold is 4-6 with a 5.06 ERA in 15 games (13 starts) with
Albuquerque. He pitched in 36 games for the Dodgers last season,
going 2-4 with a 5.48 ERA.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
