<HEADLINE> Jockey Hurt After Fall  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   OCEANPORT, N.J. (AP) -- Dean Butler was in critical condition
after his mount went down during the running of the sixth race at
Monmouth Park on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Butler was in intensive care at Monmouth Medical Center, track
officials said. Dr. Angelo Chinnici, the medical director for the
New Jersey Sports and Exposition Authority, said in a release that
Butler had blunt trauma of the head resulting in seizures.
</P>
<P>
   Butler could move all of his extremities, Chinnici said.
</P>
<P>
   Gesche, Butler's mount, had lacerations but nothing life
threatening, track officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Butler has won riding titles at Philadelphia Park and Atlantic
City Race Course.
