<HEADLINE> Capitals Re-sign Joe Murphy  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Right wing Joe Murphy signed a one-year
contract with the Washington Capitals on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Murphy, who will earn $1 million for the 2000-01 season, joined
the Capitals Feb. 10 after being claimed off waivers from Boston.
</P>
<P>
   In 29 games with Washington, Murphy had five goals and eight
assists. Overall he scored 12 goals and added 15 assists.
</P>
<P>
   The 32-year-old forward has also played for Detroit, Edmonton,
Chicago, St. Louis and San Jose during a 14-year NHL career.
</P>
<P>
   Murphy, a member of the 1990 Stanley Cup champion Edmonton
oilers, posted career-high numbers during the 1991-92 season,
recording 35 goals and 47 assists.
</P>
</TEXT>
